    dc:description "Figure 3. Anomiopus cirulito n. sp. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Ventral habitus. c) Lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3709953/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709955>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Anomiopus cirulito, n. sp. a) Head, pronotum and left tibia. b) Detail of right tibia. c) Details of metasternum in latero-ventral view. CxII = coxa II; Mt, metasternum; Mtp = metepisternum; Ms = mesepimeron." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3709955/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709957>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Vegetation and mammals at the “aguada” (wetland) Los Monifatos, the type locality of A. cirulito n. sp., in the Mayan Biosphere Reserve. Image from a camera-trap, 23 II 2015, 12:17:25 hrs, courtesy of WCS Guatemala." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3709957/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709951>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Anomiopus panamensis. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Ventral habitus. c) Lateral view. d) Details of metasternum in latero-vental view. CxII = coxa II; Mt, metasternum; Mtp = metepisternum; Ms = mesepimeron." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3709951/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

